      <h1 class='title'>Orders for transfers of tenancies of dwelling-houses</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc317-8GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_317gc' title='Col. 317GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c317GC' name='column_317gc' href='#column_317gc' rel='bookmark'>317GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04040'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_651' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        13 (1) This paragraph applies if&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) an application is made by one of the civil partners for an order under this paragraph, and</li>
        <li>(b) one of the civil partners is entitled, either in his own right or jointly with the other civil partner, to occupy a dwelling-house in Northern Ireland by virtue of a tenancy which is a tenancy mentioned in Schedule 2 to the Family Homes and Domestic Violence (Northern Ireland) Order 1998 (S.I. 1998/1071 (N.I. 6)).</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04041'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_652' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The court may make in relation to that dwelling-house any order which it could make under Part 2 of that Schedule (order transferring tenancy or switching statutory tenants) if it had power to make a property adjustment order under Part 2 of Schedule (<span class="italic">Financial relief in the High Court or a county court etc.: Northern Ireland</span>) to this Act with respect to the civil partnership.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04042'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_653' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) The provisions of paragraphs 9, 10 and 13(1) of Schedule 2 to the Family Homes and Domestic Violence (Northern Ireland) Order 1998 (payments by transferee, pre-transfer liabilities and
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_318gc' title='Col. 318GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c318GC' name='column_318gc' href='#column_318gc' rel='bookmark'>318GC</a>
        right of landlord to be heard) apply in relation to any order under this paragraph as they apply to any order under Part 2 of that Schedule.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
